Based on some research, I've found that Godin’s year runs from August 1st to July 31st, instead of January 1st to December 31st. The serial # on this guitar is 03 05 4 470, whereas the first 2 digits (03) represent the year that the guitar was built. But this is not the calendar year. Godin’s year runs from August 1st to July 31st. So the first 2 digits (03), technically represent the year ended. Digits 3 & 4 represent the week of the year that the guitar was built – remember that the Godin year is August 1st to July 31st. So week 1 is the first week of August.
